         <abstract>
            <p>Tables of the Ethiopic syllabary exist in two different orders of representation: 
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5913Abugida"/> follows the most widely used ordering system of the Semitic consonants, while
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5914Hahu"/> is inherited from the South Arabian tradition. Both tables are used in traditional schools
               for teaching reading, together with <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5905FidalaHawarya"/>.
            </p>
